pullRequest.body:
Define `ENNReal.IsConjExponent`, the `ENNReal` analogue of `Real.IsConjExponent` and `NNReal.IsConjExponent`. This will allow stating Hölder's inequality for the L1 and Linfty norms too.

From LeanAPAP

Please add the `ENNReal` version to the module docstring
Can you add a lemma about how this interacts with the coercion from `NNReal`?

```suggestion
/-- Two extended nonnegative real exponents `p, q` are conjugate and satisfy the equality
```

```suggestion
norms. Note that we permit one of the exponents to be `∞` and the other `1`. -/
```

```suggestion
/-- The conjugate exponent of `p` is `q = 1 + (p - 1)⁻¹`, so that `1/p + 1/q = 1`. -/
```
I'd prefer to have the docstring and the definition line up here - this isn't a case where the actual definition is sufficiently complicated that lying is better. I'm guessing that p/(p-1) doesn't work as the definition because of ENNReal arithmetic being weird?
Yep indeed. ENNReal arithmetic is weird: Try inputting ` p = infty`
